    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="269"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d269">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116EW/1–345</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d269fn1">Original not found. The text here printed is from a
                        copy typed in the Department of State.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-03">January 3,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum for the Secretary of State</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Please send me a brief report on the status of the proceedings before the War
                    Crimes Commission, and particularly the attitude of the U. S. representative on
                    offenses to be brought against <persName corresp="#p_HA2">Hitler</persName> and
                    the chief Nazi war criminals. The charges should include an indictment for
                    waging aggressive and unprovoked warfare, in violation of the <persName
                        corresp="#p_KFB1">Kellogg</persName> Pact.<note n="2" xml:id="d269fn2">For
                        the text, see Department of State Treaty Series No. 796, or 46 <gloss
                            target="#t_Stat1">Stat</gloss>. 2343.</note> Perhaps these and other
                    charges might be joined in a conspiracy indictment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi
                                rend="smallcaps">oosevelt</hi>]</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
